<item>
            <title>[LU-17056] sanity-sec test_30b returned 1</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17056</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/642f8dc7-dcca-4422-a550-02d5b9cedd76&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/642f8dc7-dcca-4422-a550-02d5b9cedd76&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_30b failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;checking cli2ost...found 15/16 ski connections
Error checking ski of cli2ost: expect 16, actual 15
test_30b returned 1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/96746&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/96746&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.15.1.el8_8.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/96746&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/96746&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.15.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This started failing suddenly on 2023-08-09 and never before in the past 6 months. The test itself was landed a couple of years ago, so it is likely that one on the patch landings in this timeframe caused the problem. &lt;/p&gt;









&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity-sec test_30b - test_30b returned 1&lt;/p&gt;</description>
